## Why This Is Asked
Broadcom needs engineers who can design reliable financial systems. This tests understanding of distributed systems, consistency guarantees, and production-scale message queue architecture.

## Expected Answer
Strong candidates discuss: Kafka's exactly-once semantics, idempotent producers, transactional writes, log compaction for deduplication, consumer group coordination, cross-datacenter replication (MirrorMaker), and handling network partitions. They should mention trade-offs between latency and consistency.

## Code Example
```typescript
// Kafka transactional producer setup
const producer = kafka.producer({
  transactionalId: 'financial-tx-producer',
  maxInFlightRequests: 1,
  idempotent: true
});

await producer.initTransactions();

// Exactly-once transaction
await producer.sendTransaction([
  { topic: 'transactions', messages: [{ value: transaction }] }
]);
```
